Ask yourself this: why did the stock markets rally today after Obama announced sanctions against Russians? I&rsquo;ll get back to that, but first some background.
I&rsquo;ve often said that Putin plays chess while Obama fumbles with checkers. I picture our president, chin resting on fist, brows squeezed in childlike concentration, as he carefully chooses between jumping Putin&rsquo;s piece to end the game or getting another of his pieces &ldquo;kinged.&rdquo;
Of course, Obama goes for the kingship.

Did you ever read a book and think, &ldquo;I need to tell people about this?&rdquo;
Then you didn&rsquo;t tell people about it. I mean, you didn&rsquo;t blog about it. You didn&rsquo;t &ldquo;officially&rdquo; proclaim the book &ldquo;required reading.&rdquo;
Then something happened that you knew could happen because of the book, but you don&rsquo;t get credit for calling it because you never got around to pumping the book.
That&rsquo;s how I feel today.
